The webpage above is displayed for this application. The Wappalyzer output above shows the technologies used by the target host. The target host is running Ruby according to the HTTP response header-field X-Runtime.



Since the web application converts a webpage to PDF. There must be some sort of library being used by the target. I checked the different libraries for this HTML to PDF conversion and found the libraries above. It looks like the host is running pdfkit and this is vulnerable to Command Injection.
